  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (env-gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation activities were conducted under controlled laboratory conditions (22°C, atmospheric pressure, no electromagnetic interference characterisation). The CPB deployment environment is an operating theatre in which perfusion equipment, electrocautery units, and anaesthesia machines introduce measurable EMI, ambient temperatures range 18–26°C depending on theatre protocol, and altitude-dependent pressure variation (0.85–1.01 atm) is encountered in high-altitude centres. Only a single temperature condition was tested during bench validation; humidity and EMI sensitivity studies were not performed and no environmental operating envelope bounding these parameters is documented in the submission.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-centrifugal-pump-v2",
